<paragraph blockId="26.[1876,3495,4064,4218]" lastBlockId="27.[1020,1817,369,940]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="306" pageId="26" pageNumber="305">
Included in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1843" box="[2189,2429,4117,4156]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="305" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="philippinensis">
<emphasis box="[2189,2429,4117,4156]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="305">philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and previously treated as a subspecies of 
<emphasis box="[1878,2179,4170,4209]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="305">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1843" box="[1878,2174,4170,4209]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="305" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="philippinensis">R. philippinensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
There is considerable confusion as to which populations belong to 
<heading box="[1020,1814,369,408]" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="27" pageNumber="306" reason="1">which taxon within this clade, as not all</heading>
<heading box="[1023,1817,424,463]" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="27" pageNumber="306" reason="1">
populations attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1843" box="[1524,1817,424,463]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="306" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="philippinensis">
<emphasis box="[1524,1817,424,463]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="306">R philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
<heading box="[1027,1812,476,515]" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="27" pageNumber="306" reason="1">(sensu lato) have been genetically tested.</heading>
</paragraph>
